In a 2d game, when set view scaling to viewport and aspect ratio to keep, mouse coordinates are wrong as soon as window is scaled vertically:

```
func _ready():
    set_process_input(true)

func _input(ev):
    if ev.type == InputEvent.MOUSE_MOTION:
        print(str(ev.pos))
```

When moving mouse cursor to the left edge of the screen (the gray part when background color is not changed), it says x=0 if window is not scaled, it also says x=0 when screen is only scaled horizontally, but as soon as screen is scaled vertically, x on left screen border gets negative values:

